criteria.driver_alignment:
Represent — mapped $90B across financials and compared five alternatives;  
Implement — ran code/scenario comparison and visualizations (EPS, leverage shifts);  
Validate — discussed stakeholder preferences and alignment with scenarios.

Represent — defined concrete visualization and scenario plan ("we want to visualize how the $90 billion moves through the financial statements");  
Implement — executed scenario code and produced outputs (EPS changes, share price, stake, option value, net debt) and visualizations;  
Validate — interpreted results and tied them back to goals (e.g., noting buyback is initially dilutive, comparing scenarios).

Discover — framed the allocation question and objective to minimize agency risk; 
Implement/Represent — produced a trade-off table, stakeholder impact comparisons, and EPS calculations across options; 
Reflect/Evolve — explicitly identified agency problems, stakeholder conflicts, and proposed a balanced recommendation that acknowledges trade-offs and uncertainty.

Discover — defined the decision question, objectives, inputs, and assumptions;  
Represent — described model structure, metrics (EPS, leverage, ROIC vs WACC), and visualization plan;  
Implement — showed code, parameterization, ran script, and reported numeric outputs/tables and charts;  
Validate/Evolve — ran sensitivity checks on ROIC, interpreted robustness, and refined recommendation;  
Reflect — summarized trade-offs and delivered a final split allocation recommendation.
